\par }\pard \ql \li709\ri855\widctlpar\tx8505\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin855\lin709\itap0 {Lorenzo makes an important point . . . \emdash perhaps we might consider along these lines the baleful historicity confronting vanguard and/or opposi
tional poets in this moment\emdash the intensified calls to expand the reach of the Justice Dept, the increased alliance between major internet providers and the FBI, the expansion of the Bush administration\rquote 
s targets, and the constant cries in the public discourse for \'93retaliation\'94 strongly suggest that we may be entering a period that bears comparison to the early 20th C\emdash 
\par 
\par Can we focus the direction Lorenzo\rquote s suggested in terms of the panel\rquote s original
\par }\pard\plain \s15\ql \li709\ri855\widctlpar\tx8505\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin855\lin709\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {proposal statement?  Here are some questions I\rquote m brainstormin
g after my morning caffeine jolt: How might we think of all \'93this,\'94 of \'93911\'94 and the calls for war in connection with how modernist poetic radicalism relates to contemporary
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li709\ri855\widctlpar\tx8505\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin855\lin709\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {poetic experimentation?  How might the disruptiveness of modernist poetic
