\par In her paper, \'93Another Postmodernism: Towards an Ethical Poetics,\'94 Cynthia writes:
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s16\ql \li720\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {It is not wrong to subordinate art to history\rquote s horrors, in [Alicia] Ostriker\rquote 
s view; she argues, however, not to stop there. . . . The site of . . . struggle\emdash the witnessing, the transmuting (i.e. the representing), the act of contemplative analysis (or vision, if you will) that becomes the work of art\emdash 
is a place where aesthetics and ethics can meet synergistically.(1)
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li720\ri0\sl480\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
